solution.p:
(a) 
Potential energy can be obtained by multiplying the test charge Q_2 by the potential of charge Q_1. We use the reference point at r=\infty, where potential energy is taken to be zero.

	 U \amp = Q_2 \times \phi_{\text{of Q}_1} = k\: \frac{Q_1 Q_2}{r} 
	 \amp = 9\times 10^9\times \frac{5\times 10^{-6}\times 3\times 10^{-9}}{0.04}
	 \amp  = 3.4\times 10^{-3}\:\text{J}
